<P><HI>Unparallel'd</HI> CRUELTY:</P>
<P>OR, THE TRYAL OF Captain JEANE OF <HI>BRISTOL.</HI></P>
<P>Who was convicted at the <HI>Old Bailey</HI> for the Murder of his Cabbin-Boy, who he put to Death in the mo&s;t horrid and barbarous Manner that ever was heard of.</P>
<P>To which is added, An Account of his Life and Conver&s;ation, both before and after his Condemnation; with his Dying Speech, and Behaviour at the Place of Execution.</P>
